The Location: Like most Burger King's in Urban areas, you're forced to come with modest expectations. Sadly this locations is hurt by it's lack of security. Too many people are just sitting, sleeping, lounging, playing and singing their own music. They may have purchased something, others simply just access the wifi. The upstairs is never open and I'm assuming it's for security reasons.  The Food: To keep up with the constant demand, corners are cut. It's rare that my nuggets are not overcooked. There have been times when my burger was cold. Basically this location's food suffers because the team appears to be overworked and understaffed which is a shame.  Summary: Long wait times Frustrated team members Okay food A lackluster experience overall
